I"õ<p>Recently, Iâ€™ve found <code class="highlighter-rouge">brew update</code> is extremely slow no matter I was in the office or at home.
To be honest, the network is not so good in China these days.
So, here comes the solution.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Set up a Socks5 proxy.</li>
  <li>Open the bask profile or .zshrc. Iâ€™m using ZSH, so:
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>vi $HOME/.zshrd
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Add the proxy and unproxy command into the file. For example, the socks5 URL is 127.0.0.1:1081.
    <div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>alias proxy='export all_proxy=socks5://127.0.0.1:1081'
alias unproxy='unset all_proxy'
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>Save and <code class="highlighter-rouge">source $HOME/.zshrc</code></li>
</ol>

<p>Now, use <code class="highlighter-rouge">proxy &amp;&amp; brew update &amp;&amp; unproxy</code> is resolved my problem.</p>

